OL,7,FDiscovering the existence of crude oil
OL,8,Fin the Niger Delta 68 years ago, its
OL,9,Fsubsidiary has had a near monopoly on
OL,10,Fthe extraction ever since.
OL,12,FThe local communities blame the fossil
OL,13,Ffuel giant for the chronic pollution
OL,14,Fthey are now suffering from.
OL,16,F"Shell have continually destroyed
OL,17,Feverything about us."
OL,19,FKing Godwin Okpabi remembers the
OL,20,Fdiscovery of oil in his community of
OL,21,FOgale as a warm period.
